# QR

With the QR module, users can generate QR codes with or without an image. Response will be always in base64 format.

Base URL:

```
https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode
```

## Sample

- Method: `GET`
- URL: `https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode`

### Example

```sh
curl -X 'GET' \
  'https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode' \
  -H 'accept: */*'
```

### Response

```json
{
  "text": "https://everrest.educata.dev",
  "type": "png",
  "format": "base64",
  "errorCorrectionLevel": "H",
  "imageURL": "https://github.com/educata/everrest/blob/main/docs/public/logo.png?raw=true",
  "result": "data:image/png;base64,"
}
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Educata QR Code">

## Generate

- Method: `POST`
- URL: `https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode/generate`

### Body

- `text`: string

### Example

```sh
curl -X 'POST' \
  'https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode/generate' \
  -H 'accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
  "text": "EverREST - Everything you need from REST API"
}'
```

### Response

```json
{
  "text": "EverREST - Everything you need from REST API",
  "type": "png",
  "format": "base64",
  "errorCorrectionLevel": "M",
  "result": "data:image/png;base64,"
}
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Generated qr image">

## Generate with image

- Method: `POST`
- URL: `https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode/generate_with_image`

### Body

- `text`: string
- `imageURL`: string

### Example

```sh
curl -X 'POST' \
  'https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode/generate_with_image' \
  -H 'accept: */*' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
  "text": "EverREST - Everything you need from REST API",
  "imageURL": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/educata/everrest/main/assets/images/educata-bg-transparent.png"
}'
```

### Response

```json
{
  "text": "EverREST - Everything you need from REST API",
  "type": "png",
  "format": "base64",
  "errorCorrectionLevel": "H",
  "imageURL": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/educata/everrest/main/assets/images/educata-bg-transparent.png",
  "result": "data:image/png;base64,"
}
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="sample generated image">
